# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Helix LMS — Environment Variables Template
# Copy this to .env.local and fill in all values.
# NEVER commit .env.local to git.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── Auth ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET=REPLACE_ME

# The full URL of this app (no trailing slash)
# Local dev: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://your-app.vercel.app
NEXTAUTH_URL=REPLACE_ME

# ── Google OAuth ───────────────────────────────────────
# 1. console.cloud.google.com → New Project (one per app)
# 2. APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen → External → In production
# 3. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create → OAuth 2.0 Client ID → Web application
# 4. Authorized JS origins: https://your-app.vercel.app
# 5. Authorized redirect URIs: https://your-app.vercel.app/api/auth/callback/google
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=REPLACE_ME
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=REPLACE_ME

# ── Database (Supabase) ────────────────────────────────
# supabase.com → Project → Settings → Database → Connection string
# IMPORTANT: Use simple alphanumeric password — special chars (!@#$) break URL parsing
# Pooled connection (port 6543) — for app queries
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-1-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true
# Direct connection (port 5432) — for migrations only
DIRECT_URL=postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-1-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres

# ── Supabase Public Keys ───────────────────────────────
# supabase.com → Project → Settings → API
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://[PROJECT-REF].supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_DEFAULT_KEY=REPLACE_ME
